.\" Manpage for taco.
.\" Generated by hand. Update on each release.
.TH TACO 1 "2026-05-13" "taco 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
taco \- keep your Mac awake while a long-running command finishes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B taco
.I command...
.br
.B taco
.I "\(dq command with shell features \(dq"
.br
.B taco
.B doctor
.br
.B taco
\fB\-\-help\fR | \fB\-\-version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B taco
is a one-file Bash wrapper that runs an arbitrary command and inhibits macOS sleep until that command exits. Built for the new ritual of waiting on AI coding agents (Claude Code, Codex, OpenCode, Gemini CLI, Cursor) or any long test / build / render that you don\(cqt want the system to sleep through.

The wrapped command runs via
.BR /bin/bash " " \-lc
so pipes,
.BR && ", "
environment variables, and aliases all work the way you expect. macOS
.BR caffeinate (8)
is invoked with
.B \-dim \-w \fIPID\fR
so the display, idle timer, and disk stay awake until the child exits.
.B taco
returns the same exit code as the wrapped command.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B doctor
Diagnose your local macOS setup. Reports platform, macOS version, Bash version, presence of
.BR caffeinate ", " pmset ", and " osascript ,
battery percentage, and guidance on verifying notification permission. Exits non-zero if a blocker is detected.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print
.B taco
version and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Wrap an AI coding agent:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ taco claude
.fi
.RE
.PP
Wrap a quoted shell command:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ taco "npm test"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Wrap something with shell features:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ taco "echo cooking && sleep 30 && echo done"
.fi
.RE
.PP
Diagnose your setup:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
$ taco doctor
.fi
.RE
.SH SIGNALS
.B taco
traps
.B SIGINT
and
.BR SIGTERM .
On receipt, it sends
.B SIGTERM
to the immediate child shell, cleans up
.BR caffeinate ", "
waits, and exits 130. Well-behaved subprocesses propagate the signal further; misbehaving commands may orphan grandchildren.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/bin/caffeinate
Required. Apple\(cqs power-assertion command.
.TP
.B /usr/bin/pmset
Required for the battery readout. Optional otherwise.
.TP
.B /usr/bin/osascript
Required for the macOS finish notification. Optional otherwise.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
The wrapped command succeeded.
.TP
.B 1
Usage error (missing argument, non-Darwin, or
.B caffeinate
not available).
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by
.BR SIGINT " (Ctrl+C)."
.TP
.IB N
Any other exit code is the wrapped command\(cqs own.
.SH LIMITATIONS
.B taco
does
.B not
override Apple\(cqs lid-close sleep behavior. Closing the lid will put your Mac to sleep regardless. Do not put a hot running laptop in a backpack.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR caffeinate (8),
.BR pmset (1),
.BR osascript (1),
.BR bash (1)
